    <p>I wonder what I’ll do this Labor Day weekend. Probably nothing exciting. I read this piece in the NYTimes the other day that said something like “procrastinators tend not to go on vacation because they avoid planning things” — seems to describe my vacation aversion pretty well.</p>
    <p>It’s been 32 minutes which means I have a 50/50 chance of getting my pizza RIGHT NOW or getting it in another 30.</p>
    <p>I have no ranch left. I can’t believe I done this.</p>
    <p>I have to leave my house which negates the entire point of getting delivery.</p>
